ame <i>Shirley</i> first appears in Ireland in the late 17th century, following the granting of lands to a <i>Shirley</i> family in the barony of Farney, Monaghan.","History: William Shirley (1694–1771) was born in Sussex, England, and came to MA in 1731. He rose in the colonial service, was appointed governor in 1741, and was responsible for the British capture of the French fortress of Louisbourg, Cape Breton Island, in 1745."],"variants":[{"name":"Shurley","meanings":["English: variant of   Shirley  ."]},{"name":"Sherley","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Shirley  .","Americanized form of Norwegian <b>Sjøli</b> or <b>Sjølie</b>: habitational name from a farmstead named with <i>sjø</i> ‘sea, lake’ + <i>li</i> ‘hillside’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":6,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":41,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sewallis de Shirley II was born about 1218, in Shirley, Derbyshire, England, his father, Sewallis Shirley, was 26 and his mother, Isabell Meinell, was 21. He married Isabell Meinell in 1219, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1277, at the age of 60, and was buried in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1218–1277":"umbes 1218–1277","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1218–1277":"1218–1277","1230–1296":"1230–1296","1244–Female":"1244–Surnud","1198–1228":"1198–1228","1239–1266":"1239–1266","1246–1296":"1246–1296","1246–Male":"1246–Surnu